    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The credibility assessment team accepted the simulation evidence for regulatory submission purposes on the basis that the primary ValidationResult (hemolysis-absolute-vr-01) demonstrates mean prediction error of 14.3% with Monte Carlo uncertainty bounds covering 4 of 5 operating points. The team noted that all credibility factor achieved levels fall below required levels and that six factors remain unassessed, but determined that the evidence package was sufficient for a Low assurance level submission at this stage. NOTE: The ValidationResult was generated under ModelConfiguration ansys-cfx-15-build-2024-q3 (modelVersion 2024-q3-build-2). The current model of record is 2026-q1-build-7. This version drift was not flagged during the decision review and constitutes the primary undetected weakness in this package.",
